---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="AI Leadership Playbooks | AILD.org"
  description="Leadership playbooks for AI-era decision-making, executive workflows, trust controls, and team execution."
  canonical="https://aild.org/playbooks/"
  active="playbooks"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Leadership tracks</p>
    <h1>Run AI as a leadership system, not a tool experiment.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Each playbook links strategy, decision quality, risk control, and execution.
      Start with the <a href="/learn/ai-decision-intelligence-stack-executives/">Decision Intelligence Stack</a>,
      then implement trust controls and weekly operating rhythm.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section grid-3">
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Executive Decision Playbook</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Turn ambiguous strategic questions into decision briefs</li>
        <li>Generate options with AI and compare tradeoffs explicitly</li>
        <li>Capture final decision, owner, and expected outcome</li>
      </ul>
      <p><a href="/learn/ai-assisted-strategic-review-playbook/">Open strategic review playbook</a></p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Trust vs Override Playbook</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Classify decisions by risk tier</li>
        <li>Define mandatory human review points</li>
        <li>Maintain override logs for governance and learning</li>
      </ul>
      <p><a href="/learn/trust-vs-override-framework/">Open trust framework</a></p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h3>AI-Augmented Executive Workflow</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Weekly AI brief for signals, risks, and opportunities</li>
        <li>Decision meeting rhythm with action conversion</li>
        <li>Friday review loop to calibrate quality and speed</li>
      </ul>
      <p><a href="/learn/ai-augmented-executive-workflow/">Open workflow guide</a></p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="section panel">
    <h2>90-day leadership implementation sequence</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Days 1-15: decision baseline, risk classification, governance setup.</li>
      <li>Days 16-30: pilot executive workflow with one core decision stream.</li>
      <li>Days 31-60: expand to two functions with shared quality criteria.</li>
      <li>Days 61-90: institutionalize review cadence and KPI dashboard.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Use <a href="/templates/">Templates</a>,
      <a href="/cases/">Cases</a>, and
      <a href="/research/">Research</a> as a linked execution system.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
